    <stitle>DOUBLE DIAPHRAGM ANCHORLOK SPRING BRAKE - ORANGE ALERT STROKE INDICATOR</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ORANGE ALERT STROKE INDICATOR</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
            <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
            <para>A diamond knurl band located on the service push rod between the threaded portion of the service push
                rod and the point where the service push rod enters the service housing (non-pressure housing) indicates
                that this Anchorlok double diaphragm spring brake assembly is equipped with a stroke indicator (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0401916">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0401916" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0401916" filename="../figg04/G0401916.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Spring Brake Fully Retracted</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LEADING EDGE OF DIAMOND KNURL</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. STROKE INDICATOR (ORANGE BAND)</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. PUSH ROD DISC</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. THREADED PORTION OF SERVICE PUSH ROD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The stroke indicator is an orange band located between the push rod disc and the diamond knurl on the
                service push rod.
            </para>
            <para>The orange band (stroke indicator) will only start to protrude outside of the mounting face of the
                service housing when the chamber has only 1/2 inch of stroke remaining (3/4 inch of remaining stroke for
                36 type spring brake) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0401917">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0401917" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0401917" filename="../figg04/G0401917.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. 1/2 Inch of Stroke Remaining, 3/4 Inch on 36 Type Spring Brake</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LEADING EDGE OF STROKE INDICATOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. MOUNTING FACE OF SERVICE HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. DIAMOND KNURL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
